this with just two lines of code. He gets the data and then he loads it and he's good

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:05.159
to go. So then he thinks about it and he's like, well, maybe I can use Dtree, which is

00:15:05.159 --> 00:15:12.359
a modern data visualization library available in JavaScript to kind of like create kind

00:15:12.359 --> 00:15:17.440
of like a network visualization of how all the relationship of these characters looks

00:15:17.440 --> 00:15:25.559
like. And sure enough, he uses his skill to create this particular graph, which looks

00:15:25.559 --> 00:15:30.799
actually quite compelling and interesting. As you can see on this graph that graphic

